Now to reſolve thee, why his Look makes this ſetled contract with the Earth; Thou muſt know, he has been ſo baſely baffled, jeer'd, and buffound in every quarter, as he conſorts with no Society, where diſgrace do's not meet him; telling Him, how his very Memory will be a laſting ſtaine to his Fame: a diſhonour to his Family. Doe not blame him then, for looking downward: Thou knoweſt well what the Poet ſometimes ſo divinely ſung;


God gave Men lookes to view the azure Skyes,

While Beaſts look down with earth-dejected Eyes.
